	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9761764821660><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9761764821660>Need Advice for a 16th level Wood Elf Rogue</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9761764821660#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 7th 8:08 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi, I have a 16th level Wood Elf rogue (completely untwinked)&nbsp;&nbsp;And I'm still wearing mostly leather armor.  I was wondering if anyone could give me some advice on what zones to hit to get some better equipment.  I can't kill wisps because my main piercer is a FS spear, and I can't afford a dragoon dirk (they go for about 100pp on Torvon from what I've seen).  Anyway, right now I've been killing Dervs for bronze, and Crocs for xp (I'm in the NRo/oasis area).  Any advice would be much appreciated.<br><br>Malishael - 16th season rogue Torvon  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
