<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=97642653019293></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97642653019293><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97642653019293>RE: Need Advice for a 16th level Wood Elf Rogue</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97642653019293#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=5639><span id= >CyllusBaneheart</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 10th 5:35 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK Serpentine bracer would be great to try to get.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has good +DEX which, as a Rogue, oyu want.  Also, you certainly do want to use 1hb  1hs  bows  AND  throwing knives.   Rogue's can use many weapons, and throwing weapons scores an occaisional critical hit.  Get a few levels higher (to 18) and head over to South Karana, get a bind at Rathe Arena, there will be plenty of shouts to sell dagger of dropping there and plenty of Aviak groups to join in.  Just save your pennies till you hit 18 and try to find Banded armor, it goes for 1pp per AC and for a Rogue it's actually pretty good armor at low to mid 20's, unless you can find +DEX stuff.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
