	   <tr><td colspan=2>As it has been mentioned before, I would suggest that you pick up a dagger of dropping or some other relatively cheap peircer for your first hand. Then what I did for about three levels, between 13 and 16, I killed wisps, green or whatever. On Luclin, those greater lightsones still sell for about 8pp a pop, and for normal lightsones, like 1 to 2pp. That's not bad considering that every one you kill will probably drop one or the other. (Save for when they want to drop burned out lightstones... Grr.) In all honesty, I made 100pp in an hour that way. That's how I got ahold of a dragoon dirk at level 13. Then by 18 I had a stilletto of the bloodclaw, and a serrated bone dirk. There wasn't even any twinking with me, unless you want to count a fine steel rapier or something. <br><br> - Gaeweina of Luclin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
