	   <a name=9753088344131></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9753088344131><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9753088344131>IMAO...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=9753088344131#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2257><span id=Scholar>Kaguk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>26 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 27th 2:07 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It really depends.&nbsp;&nbsp;I like hard backstabs and not getting hit a lot...  So I go for STR (increases backstab damage) and AGI (increases AC and enhances chance to dodge, parry, etc).  As you get higher the less you should be taking hits, so I'd reccomend more STR than AGI.  DEX is pretty important as many rogue items proc (SBD, SBC, SSoY, etc) not to mention that it doesn't do you much good to backstab hard if you don't hit them with the backstab.  STA isn't very important to buff because like I said, you shouldn't be taking too many hits.  For a wood elf rogue, I would put 20 into STR and 10 into DEX.  IMAO.<br><br>-Aenar Velg`arn, 28th Dark Elf Rogue<br> Taludor Magness, 20th Barbarian Rogue<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
