<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=97257122923803></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97257122923803><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97257122923803>RE: Need DE Rogue Advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97257122923803#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 26th 10:40 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a 10th DE Rogue and here are some of my experiences:&nbsp;&nbsp;First, I play on a team PvP server which may have an effect on some things, but it's much better roleplay and I really like it.  I did the Dark Shield of Ebon quest several times, you get experience for that, which some say can carry you to sixth level.  The Shield is sellable to vendors and re-obtainable, too.  Being short on cash, as I was and you no doubt are, I recommend buying a small sewing kit (in fact, the large sewing kits are not available in Neriak), and making your own set of patchwork armor.  It's pretty easy, not too expensive to do, and it looks cool.  If you want to really get into tailoring, you should pick up a large sewing kit from the nearest vendor, which is Spoolie Gee in a hut in North Ro.  You will have to sneak/hide to get past the guards, but you will feel like James Bond, swelling with pride at your own stealth and cunning abilities as you glide back to Neriak with your sparkling new LARGE sewing kit.  The reason you want a large kit is because the small kits only hold two components and some items require more than two components in order to make them, such as raw silk robes and raw silk leggings for casters.  I took up fishing, too, because fish bait is cheaper than food, and the fish you catch are edible.  It's simply the cheapest food you can get except for summoned food, and foraged food, neither of which you can do.  So, having made myself an almost complete set of patchwork armor, I longed to make the other pieces to make the set complete.  But not all the patterns necessary for a complete set are available in Neriak.  They missing patterns are, however, available in the Feerrot.  Somewhere along in that period of my life I was PK'ed by a ranger with a bow.  He just plugged away at me and I was goosed rather quickly.  That stuck in my mind.  Back at the rogue guild later on I noticed a vendor selling bows and arrows, so I picked one up and fooled around with it.  Long story short, I ran through all the arrows and went back to the vendor for more, but he was out.  When I shouted "where can I get some cheap arrows", the response was "you can make your own with a fletching kit".  Fletching kits are available in Freeport, I hear, and in the Feerrot.  That was when I knew I had to leave home for a long journey to the Feerrot to find the missing armor patterns and to pick up a fletching kit and make some more arrows for myself.  I sneak/hide-ed myself all the way there, slow but fairly hazard-free.  Let me recommend a move to the Feerrot to you, and here's why.  The missing tailoring patterns are there, if you want them, fletching kits and fletching supplies are there, if you get into that, it is a place that is not usually over-hunted, as is Nektulos Forest.  Particularly, there is a set of ruins in the Feerrot which has to be about the best place in the game to gather bonechips from skeletons.  Bonechips can be sold from 2pp-5pp per stack, depending on the market.  And you will get good experience from all the kills.   There are also lots of lizardmen to kill in front of the entrance to Cazic-Thule.  Black wolves and shadow wolves abound in the certain spots to provide you with ruined pelts for your tailoring.  South Ro and Oasis are not far away for your levelling up into your 20's, then you can come back to CazicThule and group in there.  I got someone to bind me in Oggok and have been doing rather well there.  Oh, and I forgot, whenever, while in Neriak, I made a trip to my guild, in the zone in which the guild is found there is a moat that you run by on the way to the guild.  I always jumped into the water on my way to and from the guild so as to practice my swimming.  I think you should be careful to always exploit an opportunity to increase any skill you have.  You're not a caster and must rely much more heavily on your skills than non-casters.  Furthermore, a good rogue is a well-rounded rogue, a jack-of-all-trades, in my view.  Lastly, you should always be on the lookout for a money making enterprise.  Listen for /tells from people who need a favor:  "Looking for someone to run into Neriak and get me some food, I'm an Iksar and I am KOS"  You can easily walk away with a nice jingle in your pocket.  Also, large sewing kits not available in Neriak, nor certain patterns, nor fletching kits, nor fletching supplies?  Hmmm.  Good luck to you brother!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
