	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 11th 3:48 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.48]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Best place I've found to raise safe fall, without taking any damage is in Lake Rathe.&nbsp;&nbsp;The hill directly behind that monk Johnas.  You can raise your safe fall 5 points in under 2 minutes there.  Just run to the top and run down...<br><br>Here are some other Good places...<br>   The Side of the Ridge in East Karana on the way to high pass.  Be sure to do this on the lower side after the trail does the cross-over.  On the higher side it's a long fall with no chance to stop yourself midway.  <br>   Several Pillars in the Oasis Area.<br>   Several Cliff Sides in the Cauldron area before Unrest.<br><br>What you're looking for is a single place where you run down and make 3-4 skill checks right after each other.  Avoid at all costs those ramps where you run and drop, run around and drop again, making 1 skill check at each pass.  This is a complete waste of time which could be better used killing things.<br>   Also be careful at the lower levels, some of the recommend places will get you killed if your safe fall isn't high enough to start with.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
